  "title": "Business Development Executive (Data Centre) | $5,500",
  "description": "<h2>🚀 Business Development Executive | $5,500</h2><p>📍 <strong>Location:</strong> Sembawang<br />🕘 <strong>Working Hours:</strong> Monday – Friday, Office Hours<br />💰 <strong>Salary:</strong> Up to <strong>$5,500</strong> (commensurate with skills, experience & qualifications)</p><p>We are expanding and looking for a <strong>dynamic, outgoing Business Development professional</strong> to join our growing regional team. This is a newly created role offering strong exposure to <strong>Data Centre projects</strong>, regional markets, and collaboration with industry leaders in a fast-evolving environment.</p><h2>🌟 Why Join?</h2><ul><li><p>Exposure to <strong>regional Data Centre & AI-related projects</strong></p></li><li><p>Work closely with <strong>senior stakeholders and industry leaders</strong></p></li><li><p>Strong opportunities for <strong>career growth and development</strong></p></li><li><p>Stable MNC environment with long-term expansion plans</p></li></ul><h2>🔧 Key Responsibilities</h2><ul><li><p>Develop and execute strategies to penetrate new regional markets</p></li><li><p>Build and maintain strong relationships with Data Centre operators, M&E contractors, and consultants</p></li><li><p>Support sales and marketing initiatives including client visits, exhibitions, factory visits, and training sessions</p></li><li><p>Review commercial submissions and power train unit (PTU) scopes</p></li><li><p>Prepare business tracking, reports, and weekly progress updates (Excel-based)</p></li><li><p>Design and develop marketing materials</p></li><li><p>Engage clients through networking, meetings, and client entertainment (including after office hours)</p></li></ul><h2>👤 Requirements</h2><ul><li><p>Diploma or Bachelor’s Degree in <strong>Electrical / Electronic Engineering</strong>, or <strong>Marketing / Business</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>3–5 years</strong> of relevant working experience</p></li><li><p><strong>Data Centre or electrical industry experience</strong> is a strong advantage</p></li><li><p>Outgoing, confident, and enjoys networking</p></li><li><p>Strong interpersonal, presentation, and communication skills</p></li><li><p>Well-organised, proactive, and able to perform under pressure</p></li><li><p>Proficient in Microsoft Office (Excel, Word, PowerPoint)</p></li><li><p>Willingness to <strong>travel within the region</strong></p></li></ul><h2>🎯 Ideal Candidate</h2><p>You are commercially savvy, relationship-driven, and enjoy building connections in a technical environment. If you thrive in a fast-paced industry and are keen to grow within the <strong>Data Centre market</strong>, this role is for you.<br /></p><p>📩 <strong>Apply Now</strong></p><p>Send your resume (MS Word format) to:</p><p>📱 WhatsApp / Telegram: 8509 0409</p><p>Please include your availability, notice period and expected salary in your application.</p><p><em>Only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</em></p><p>—</p><p>Annie Hoang (R25158747)</p><p>CREW by HRnet |HRnet Ventures Pte Ltd </p><p>EA24C2435</p>",
